# Goal Description

The goal is to update some existing labels in the app and introduce a brand new "Meditate" section. This new section will feature a recorded meditation and functionality to track the user's meditation progress, either manually or automatically upon completion of the audio session. 

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Regarding the "recorded meditation" and "visuals of tracking" you mentioned: you attached a photo of a handwritten notebook about Chakras and frequencies, but the audio file and the screenshot of the tracking visuals seem to be missing from your request. 
> For now, I will use a **placeholder audio file** and design a **standard tracking visual** (like a calendar or progress bar). Please provide the actual audio file or its link, and any specific design details for the tracking visuals if you have them!

## Open Questions

1. Do you want the new "Meditate" screen to replace the existing "2-minute reset" meditation panel on the Dashboard, or should they both exist?
2. How would you like the meditation progress to be tracked? (e.g., number of sessions completed, total minutes meditated, a streak counter, or a calendar view of days meditated). Currently, I'll plan for a session counter and a visual calendar representation.

